Syntax : initialization
          while (condition)
          {
            Statement ;
            update ;
          }

- While loop has a condition with the block which contains statement.
- The condition must be a boolean type.
- Initialization fro while loop must be done before starting while loops.
- After all the statement are executed, An update statement must be provided.
** THE WHILE LOOP MINIMUM OUTPUT IS 0. **

--WORKING--

  - First condition check before the statement executed.
  - If condition evaluate true the statement of block executed along with update.
  - then control goes to the condition to check whether the condition is true or to redo this process 
    until condition becomes false.

  
